The United Democratic Alliance led by deputy president William Ruto on February 1, released a breakdown of how much aspirants will pay to participate in the nomination exercise. Those seeking the presidency are required to pay Sh1,000,000 for men, while females and youths will part with Sh500,000. Females and youths are paying half the amount of men in each elective seat while peopleÂ living with disabilities have been exempted from paying anything for the nomination exercise. The group will participate in the nomination exercise for free.